channel.description:
[b]Description;[/b] To teach you how to add a character limit to a textarea

[b]Difficulty;[/b] 2.5/10

[b]Browsers Supported;[/b] All, I have only tested on IE8 and Chrome.

[b]Procedure;[/b]

Firstly put this in your <head> section of your webpage
[code=javascript]<script language = "Javascript"> 

function taLimit()  
{ 
    var taObj=event.srcElement; 
    if (taObj.value.length==taObj.maxLength*1) return false; 
} 

function taCount(visCnt)  
{  
    var taObj=event.srcElement; 
    if (taObj.value.length>taObj.maxLength*1) taObj.value=taObj.value.substring(0,taObj.maxLength*1); 
    if (visCnt) visCnt.innerText=taObj.maxLength-taObj.value.length; 
} 
</script>[/code]

Now put this where you want your TextArea

[code=html]
<textarea onkeypress="return taLimit()" onkeyup="return taCount(myCounter)"  
name=Description rows=10 wrap=physical cols=30 maxLength="300"></textarea>
<br>
<b>You have</b> <span id=myCounter>300</span> <b>Characters remaining</b>
[/code]

This will limit the textarea to 300 characters and add a message below that says  You have *** characters remaining.

Enjoy!
